Please note, that in some cases no following AfterUpdate can be called.

virtual bool imod::IObserver::IsModelAttached ( const IModel *  modelPtr  )  const [pure virtual]

Check if specified model is attached.

pointer to model object. If this pointer is NULL, any model is meaned.

Returns:
true, if modelPtr is attached yet to this observer, false otherwise.

Implemented in imod::CMultiModelBridgeBase, imod::CMultiModelObserverBase, and imod::CSingleModelObserverBase.

virtual bool imod::IObserver::OnAttached ( IModel *  modelPtr  )  [pure virtual]

This call back function will be called, if an observable object is about to be attached.

This function returns a true, if observable object is accepted by the implementation logic of the observer, otherwise the function returns a false.
